## typed event models  (pseudo-Python, lives in `arc_guard_core.lifecycle.events`)

```python
@dataclass(frozen=True)
class LifecycleEventBase:
    id: str          # ulid; sortable by time
    parent_id: str | None
    seq: int         # monotonic per rid
    ts: datetime
    rid: str         # api-wrapper correlation

@dataclass(frozen=True)
class RequestStarted(LifecycleEventBase):
    route: str       # '/v1/chat/completions' | '/v1/guard'
    model: str | None
    msg_count: int | None
    input_size_bytes: int

@dataclass(frozen=True)
class PreProcessStarted(LifecycleEventBase):
    correlation_id: str
    decision_id: str

@dataclass(frozen=True)
class StageRan(LifecycleEventBase):
    stage: Literal['validate','defend','classify',
      'deception_inspect','sanitize','route','execute',
      'refusal','verify','rehydrate','decision_emit','report']
    duration_ms: float
    status: Literal['ok','err','skipped']

@dataclass(frozen=True)
class InspectorRan(LifecycleEventBase):
    name: str         # 'InjectionInspector', 'PresidioInspector', ...
    duration_ms: float
    findings_count: int

@dataclass(frozen=True)
class FindingProduced(LifecycleEventBase):
    entity_type: str  # 'EMAIL_ADDRESS', 'INJECTION', ...
    span: tuple[int, int]
    score: float
    risk_level: int   # 1=LOW .. 4=CRITICAL
    inspector: str

@dataclass(frozen=True)
class SanitizationApplied(LifecycleEventBase):
    entity: str
    placeholder: str
    span: tuple[int, int]
    # placeholder→original map NOT in event; lives only inside pipeline

@dataclass(frozen=True)
class PolicyResolved(LifecycleEventBase):
    max_risk: str
    resolved_action: str
    router: str       # 'default' | 'rule_based:<name>'

@dataclass(frozen=True)
class StrategyExecuted(LifecycleEventBase):
    strategy: str     # 'RedactStrategy', 'BlockStrategy', ...
    finding_id: str   # links back to FindingProduced.id
    text_after_size: int  # NOT raw text by default

@dataclass(frozen=True)
class DecisionEmitted(LifecycleEventBase):
    action: str
    max_risk: str
    decision_id: str
    bypass_reason: str | None

@dataclass(frozen=True)
class BackendCalled(LifecycleEventBase):
    backend: str      # 'echo' | 'ollama' | 'openai'
    url: str
    payload_msg_count: int

@dataclass(frozen=True)
class BackendResponded(LifecycleEventBase):
    duration_ms: float
    http_status: int
    response_msg_chars: int
    response_finish_reason: str | None
    swap_origin_id: str | None  # links to PayloadRewritten.id

@dataclass(frozen=True)
class RefusalProduced(LifecycleEventBase):
    refusal_code: str
    human_message_chars: int
    decision_id: str  # links to DecisionEmitted.decision_id

@dataclass(frozen=True)
class RequestCompleted(LifecycleEventBase):
    blocked: bool
    pre_action: str
    post_action: str | None
    total_duration_ms: float
```

## cross-reference catalog (event-to-event links)

These are **non-parent** links — `parent_id` builds the tree, these add the *causal* edges that turn the tree into a true DAG.

| Source field | Points at | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `StrategyExecuted.finding_id` | `FindingProduced.id` | which finding drove the redact/block |
| `RefusalProduced.decision_id` | `DecisionEmitted.decision_id` | trace refusal back to the decision it implements |
| `BackendResponded.swap_origin_id` | `PayloadRewritten.id` | what payload was sent vs what came back |

Adding more is cheap (add a field; sink stores it; dashboard reads it). But each new cross-ref is a contract — once dashboards consume it, removing it breaks them. Recommend: ship these three in the first spec, add more only when a concrete dashboard view needs them.
